{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} {{Use British English|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox theatre group | name = Forced Entertainment | image = | imagesize = | caption = | formed = 1984 | disbanded = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | genre = | location = Sheffield | members = | ArtisticDirector = [[Tim Etchells]] | notable = | homepage = {{URL|www.forcedentertainment.com}} }}
'''Forced Entertainment''' is an [[experimental theatre]] company based in [[Sheffield]], England, founded by [[Tim Etchells]] in 1984.<ref name="bbc-radio-4">{{cite web|url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01k12qv | date = 18 June 2012 | accessdate = 18 November 2013 | publisher = [[BBC]] | title = Forced Entertainment}}</ref><ref name="aesthetica">{{cite web|url = http://www.aestheticamagazine.com/experimental-theatre-provoking-ideas | accessdate = 27 October 2013 | last = Fairweather | first = Shona Fairweather | publisher = [[Aesthetica magazine]] | title = Experimental Theatre: Provoking Ideas}}</ref><ref name="robert-avila">{{cite news |url = http://www.sfbg.com/2012/12/04/london-diary | date = 4 December 2012 | accessdate = 18 November 2013 | first= Robert |last= Avila | publisher = [[San Francisco Bay Guardian]] | title = London diary}}</ref><ref name="mary-brennan">{{cite news |url = http://www.heraldscotland.com/arts-ents/stage/forced-entertainment-storm-back-with-two-shows.22362114 | date = 7 October 2013 | accessdate = 18 November 2013 | first= Mary |last= Brennan | publisher = [[Sunday Herald]] | title = Forced Entertainment Storm back with two shows}}</ref>
==Details and history== Forced Entertainment originally focused on making and touring theatre performances before expanding to long durational performance, live art, video and digital media.<ref name="mary-brennan" /><ref name="lyn-gardner-guardian-crazy" /> Their work has been presented throughout the UK and Europe<ref name="mary-brennan" /> as well as Australia, Japan, Canada and the US.<ref name="aesthetica" /><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.britishcouncil.org/arts-performanceinprofile-2010-forced-entertainment.htm | accessdate = 27 October 2013 | title = Forced Entertainment - Performance in Profile 2010| publisher = British Council=|publisher british council=}}</ref> They develop projects using a collaborative process – devising work as a group through improvisation, experimentation and debate.<ref name="aesthetica" /><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/funding/browse-regularly-funded-organisations/npo/forced-entertainment-ltd/ | accessdate = 27 October 2013 | publisher = Arts Council England | title = Forced Entertainment Ltd}}</ref> Their core members are [[Tim Etchells]] (artistic director),<ref name="bbc-radio-4" /><ref name="aesthetica" /> Richard Lowdon (designer and performer)<ref name="aesthetica" /> and performers Robin Arthur,<ref name="aesthetica" /><ref name="joyce-mcmillan">{{cite news |url = http://www.scotsman.com/what-s-on/theatre-comedy-dance/theatre-review-tomorrow-s-parties-glasgow-1-3138994 | date = 12 October 2013 | accessdate = 18 November 2013 | first= Joyce |last= McMillan | publisher = [[The Scotsman]] | title = Theatre review: Tomorrow's Parties, Glasgow}}</ref> Claire Marshall,<ref name="aesthetica" /><ref name="joyce-mcmillan" /> Cathy Naden<ref name="aesthetica" /> and Terry O'Connor,<ref name="aesthetica" /> who have all been with the company from the start.<ref name="bbc-radio-4" /><ref name="lyn-gardner-guardian-war">{{cite news |url = https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2009/feb/23/forced-entertainment-sheffield | date = 23 February 2009 | accessdate = 18 November 2013 | first= Lyn |last= Gardner | publisher = [[The Guardian]] | title = 'We are waging a war'}}</ref>
A book was published about them in 2004, ''"Not Even a Game Anymore": The Theatre of Forced Entertainment''.<ref name="not-even-a-game-anymore-amazon" /> In 2012 [[BBC Radio 4]] aired a programme following their creative process developing, writing and rehearsing ''The Coming Storm''.<ref name="bbc-radio-4" />
